The paper deals with the classification of EEG signals using machine learning techniques, which falls under the broad category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of marginalized discrete wavelet transform (mDWT) coefficients in EEG signal classification suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) or neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper involves feature selection, which is a common technique in computer vision (cs.CV) and signal processing (cs.SI). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CV, and cs.SI, in that order.
